metadata.synopsis: Japanese photographers and the "Wizard of Oz" munchkins confuse a hotel rendezvous of German and Japanese spies.

reviews: Before the success of Princess Leia in her metal bikini, here Fisher is stripped down to her underwear - one of the only notable elements of this highly forgettable film.
I maintain that, while it may be a failure, it's an ambitious failure.
This movie is in desperate need of an ace farceur like Preston Sturges.
A peculiar career choice for Fisher.
Mr. Rash has earnestness and a touch of eccentricity, but he doesn't have the lighthearted wit to keep this kind of comedy working.
